1. What is Git

Git is a distributed version control system used to track changes in files and coordinate work between multiple engineers.

Key features:

Tracks file changes

Maintains history of code

Enables collaboration

Allows branching and merging

Works locally and remotely

Important concepts:

Repository: project tracked by Git

Commit: snapshot of project state

Branch: parallel line of development

Remote: hosted repository (GitHub/GitLab)

2. Installing Git

Check if Git is installed:

git --version

Install Git:

Ubuntu/Debian:

sudo apt install git

RHEL/CentOS:

sudo yum install git -y

Verify installation:

git --version
3. Initial Git Configuration

Git requires identity information for commits.

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
git config --list

